  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, there isn't definitive public information detailing who the original choice was to portray Bob Lee Swagger in the 2007 movie **\"Shooter.\"** Mark Wahlberg ultimately secured the role, bringing his action-star persona to the character based on Stephen Hunter's novel *\"Point of Impact.\"*\n\nWhile casting processes for major films often involve considering several actors, specific details about other actors who might have been in contention for the role of Bob Lee Swagger haven't been widely disclosed or confirmed by reliable sources. Speculation might suggest that other prominent action actors of the time, such as **Keanu Reeves** or **Matt Damon**, could have been contenders, but there's no concrete evidence to support this.\n\nIt's possible that interviews with the film's director, Antoine Fuqua, or with Mark Wahlberg himself might shed more light on the casting decisions, but as of the latest available information, Mark Wahlberg is recognized as the principal actor and wasn't publicly reported to have been a second choice.\n\nIf you're interested in more in-depth details, I recommend checking out interviews from the time of the film's release or reputable film industry publications that might have covered the casting process in greater detail.",
